  "function_path": "source/common/router/upstream_request.cc",
  "function_name": "UpstreamRequest::onPoolReady",
  "justification": "This function initializes an upstream request after the connection pool provides a connection. It takes ownership of a GenericUpstream via move semantics, a shared pointer to the upstream host description, a reference to the connection's address provider, a reference to the pool's stream info, and an optional HTTP protocol version. The function performs all specified side effects: records connection pool callback latency, reports successful connection to the host's outlier detector, selects upstream host and records protocol, copies connection timing data and stream count, sets up filter state and upstream address information, synchronizes upstream and downstream byte meters, defers or immediately starts per-try timeout based on downstream status, registers downstream watermark callbacks for backpressure propagation, computes and starts the max stream duration timer, rewrites the Host header if auto-host-rewrite is enabled and hostname is non-empty, emits an upstream pool-ready access log entry, and invokes all registered upstream-connection-established callbacks."
}

